### Current behavior

We're working on upgrading to Cypress 13, and have run into an issue that looks to be a bug. We're intercepting a request as such: 
```js
cy.intercept('DELETE', 'URL', (req) => {
                    req.reply({
                        statusCode: 400
                    });
                }).as('alias');
```


In our app we are looking at the method of the request to decide on which error message to display. Specifically we look at response.request.method (this is just looking at the object returned when running the request via axios). But for some reason in Cypress 13, that field along with response.request.url and response.request.id are missing, as opposed to when running in Cypress 11 those three fields are there. 
          
